name: Vershyna and Bakhmut with assault actions

column4: A Russian offensive into the town was repelled (3). Russian forces claim to be moving north along the outskirts of the village without really being able to enter it. They are painting this as some sort of way of surrounding the town and attacking Bakhmut from the flank
column5: but if you look at the map that makes absolutely no sense whatsoever. Russian forces were also bragging today that they managed to shoot an enormous warehouse with artillery after having repeatedly missing for days. A+ Gunnery. They account their success to having spotters closer to the building. Apparently the guns were missing by so much you couldn’t see the landing positions from further away.
